4. Reporting style - Focus on features of reports

Charges dropped in strawberry needle case

Busuu

It has been reported that the food contamination case 
against My Ut Trinh was dropped after three years.

The 53 year old was informed that the trial 
would no longer go ahead. At the time, 
it was alleged that she had inserted needles 
into strawberries grown on the farm she supervised.

“The prosecution have indicated they would no 
longer go ahead with the charges against you”, 
the Crown informed Ms Trinh. It is said that 
Ms Trinh was pleased with the outcome as 
her lawyer stated, “She thanks everyone who 
believed in her innocence.”

In September 2018, 230 police reports were filed 
of needle contamination, prompting supermarkets 
to pull their supply of strawberries from their shelves.

According to the article, what happened to Ms Trinh?
She was not charged for any crimes.

What was Ms Trinh's reaction to the prosecution's decision?
She was happy and grateful for the support.

the prosecution တရားစွဲမယ်။
The prosecution dropped the case against her.

Which part of the article does NOT tell you that Ms Trinh's case was dropped?
the last paragraph

It was stated that Ms Trinh was pleased that the case was dropped.

It was claimed that 230 police reports of fruit tampering were filed in 2018.

Ms Trinh's lawyer
"She thanks everyone who believed in her innocence.”

the Crown
“The prosecution have indicated they would no longer go ahead with the charges against you.”

Charges dropped in strawberry needle case

